# Summary

The Payments Domain supports a small set of high-value use cases that together cover the entire payment lifecycle: initiation, processing, failure handling, refunds, reconciliation, and querying.

Each use case is tightly connected to domain rules, events, and entities to ensure traceability and consistency across the system. The separation of concerns across domains ensures scalability, maintainability, and clear ownership boundaries.
